; lxa Startup-Sequence
; Default startup script for lxa AmigaOS-compatible environment
;
; This file is executed when the system boots.
; Uncomment and modify the commands below as needed.

; Display welcome message
Echo ""
Echo "Welcome to lxa - Linux Amiga Emulation Layer"
Echo "AmigaOS-compatible environment running on Linux"
Echo ""

; Set up command search path
; This adds SYS:C to the command search path
; Path SYS:C ADD

; Display current directory
; Echo "Current directory:"
; CD

; Run any additional startup commands here
; For example:
; Execute S:User-Startup

; End of Startup-Sequence
